{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-03-09T02:34:24Z","content":"In 2003 my husband was a tow truck operator and was hooking up a vehicle along an interstate in PA and was hit by a vehicle going 55-60 mph and now has permanent nerve damage from this and can no longer work in that profession. He is always in pain because a motorist could not move over or even slow down! That motorist will never know how his actions have forever affected my whole family.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Carol Lynn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85041614"},{"created_at":"2014-03-08T15:47:40Z","content":"emergency personnel get hurt every year because idiots don't know how to follow the rules... I have friends that are emergency personnel and I would hate to see them get hurt. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"chelsea boyle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85000831"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T04:20:59Z","content":"My son-in-law was hit by a driver who was not paying attention and changed his life forever. Tow truck drivers should be given the same courtesy as police, fire and ambulance vehicles/drivers. They are just as important as the emergency responders. Too many have been hurt due to people being very inconsiderate and not slowing down or moving over out of the way of these vehicles.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Margaret Hohn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64408635"},{"created_at":"2014-03-08T04:46:09Z","content":"they also have families too.  I am sorry safety should be no one","like_count":1,"author_name":"jennifer fletcher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/84964942"},{"created_at":"2014-03-29T20:30:54Z","content":"because I was hit by a car 11 years ago while a hooking up a car","like_count":1,"author_name":"wally lynn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87852014"}]}
